Renowned rapper Kiernan Forbes, popularly known as AKA, has been shot and killed in Durban. #eNCA speaks to KZN police Spokesperson Robert Netshiunda. #eNCA #DStv403  Editor's Note: This is a developing story. This article has been updated.  JOHANNESBURG - Renowned rapper Kiernan Forbes, popularly known as AKA, has been shot and killed in Durban. The famed hip hop star was just 35. AKA had been in eThekwini for a performance. KwaZulu-Natal police say the multi-award winner and an unidentified man were leaving a restaurant on Florida Road when the suspects opened fire on them. Two murder dockets are being investigated.  Renowned rapper Kiernan Forbes, popularly known as AKA, has been shot and killed in Durban. #eNCA speaks to Garrith Jamieson from ALS Paramedics Medical Services. They're part of the team that responded to the shooting. #eNCA #DStv403  Super Mega is known for hits like Fela in Versace, Composure and Run Jozi. He'd won many accolades throughout his career, including Best Male Artist Award at the SA Music Awards in 2012. He was nominated for Best International Act twice at the BET awards. KZN Sport, Arts and Culture MEC Amanda Bani-Mapena has sent her condolences to the family and friends of the murdered rapper. pic.twitter.com/3DONLbS4yX Media Statement - Dsac on the Passing of Aka 11 February 2023_230211_082746 by eNCA.com on Scribd 